  "prompt": "How many numbers between 200 and 300 are such which are divisible by 13?",
  "response": "To find how many numbers between 200 and 300 are divisible by 13, we first identify the smallest number divisible by 13 within the range and then the largest number divisible by 13 within the range.\n\n1. Find the smallest number divisible by 13 greater than or equal to 200:\n\\[13 \\times 16 = 208 \\]\nThus, 208 is the first number divisible by 13 within our range.\n\n2. Find the largest number divisible by 13 less than or equal to 300:\n\\[13 \\times 23 = 299 \\]\nThus, 299 is the last number divisible by 13 within our range.\n\nNext, we need to count all the numbers divisible by 13 between 208 and 299, inclusive. This is an arithmetic sequence where the general term is given by \\(a_n = 208 + (n-1) \\times 13\\).\n\nSolving for \\(n\\) when \\(a_n = 299\\):\n\\[208 + (n-1) \\times 13 = 299\\]\n\\[ (n-1) \\times 13 = 299 - 208 \\]\n\\[ (n-1) \\times 13 = 91 \\]\n\\[ n-1 = \\frac{91}{13} \\]\n\\[ n-1 = 7 \\]\n\\[ n = 8 \\]\n\nThus, there are 8 numbers between 200 and 300 that are divisible by 13.",
